# Ignore everything
/*

# But not these files and directories
!/.gitignore
!/.claude-plugin/
!/agents/
!/commands/
!/skills/
!/LICENSE
!/FLOOR.md
!/docs/
!/scripts/
!/tests/
!/dist/
dist/standalone-skills/
!/.github/
!/action.yml

# /assess output: we dogfood /assess on this repo, so its compounding wiki and
# latest report ARE tracked (the report, both SVGs, the stats baseline for the
# next run's diff, and the index/log/hotspots wiki). The transient sidecars are
# regenerated every run, so they stay ignored to keep diffs clean.
!/.assess/
/.assess/run-context.json
/.assess/complexity-stats.prior.json
/.assess/.cache/

# Still ignore .DS_Store files everywhere
**/.DS_Store

# Python tooling artefacts under the allowlisted dirs above (scripts/, etc.)
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.venv/
**/uv.lock
**/.coverage
**/.coverage.*

# Ignore nested CLAUDE.md files (e.g. user's personal config when they
# clone this into ~/.claude/). The root /CLAUDE.md is re-allowlisted
# below - it's the in-repo agent contract.
.claude/
**/CLAUDE.md
!/CLAUDE.md

# Test fixtures intentionally named CLAUDE.md / .claude/skills to exercise the
# instruction-bloat penalty and skills-delegation detection. Re-include them so
# the grader tests have committed inputs on CI.
!/skills/assess/tests/fixtures/lean_with_skills/CLAUDE.md
!/skills/assess/tests/fixtures/lean_with_skills/.claude/
# skill-forge's instruction-file calibration fixture: a deliberately flawed
# always-loaded CLAUDE.md with a count-surface trap (issue #226). Committed so
# the contract test has an input on CI.
!/skills/skill-forge/tests/fixtures/flawed-instruction-file/CLAUDE.md